data.title: Excellent Food
data.text: We were directed to this restaurant by the staff at the hotel at which we were staying. The restaurant was a three minute walk away and is located in a nearby strip mall. We were met by a young waitress and taken to a table. We ordered two different curries, nam bread, rice, chutney and papadum. We asked for spicy and indeed when the food arrived it was very spicy . The taste was wonderful and the spice was just right for our taste. The young waitress is a student at the local community college and came from Nepal to study mechanical engineering. She was delightful!

data.title: Good and clean food
data.text: I like the food a lot. Ordered Paneer Butter Masala, Malai Kofta and Mix daal, Both curries were very authentic, daal was not so good. Also they served it quickly and hot so overall good experience.

data.title: A wonder filled taste of India
data.text: Had to be in Lakewood and found this little gem. It had been a few years for Me and good Indian food. This was a long deserved find. I remember the rice being stickier and the naan being more plentiful ,but this was still a nice treat.

data.title: Fantastic spicy food.
data.text: We got spicy lentil stew and a vegetable curry late at night as we checked in.  Fantastic!  Super convenient location.  Will surely patronize again.

data.title: Exotic tastes in Lakewood!
data.text: After many times of passing this hidden restaurant in Lakewood we finally decided to give it a try.  We were craving something different but weren't sure about Indian food since neither of us were familiar with it.  What a great surprise we stumbled upon.  Many times when we try out restaurants claiming to serve authentic food from other regions of the  world, we enter places that just don't cut it, many have bland food with generic atmospheres.  After entering Great India, we were pleasantly surprised with Indian music and friendly staff that created a wonderful dining experience.  We did not realize they had a buffet option and decided to try it.  The food was great, several different rice and chicken dishes to choose from.  I tried a little from each dish and every dish was flavorful and not too spicy.  The chicken was tender and cooked in a sauce.  I actually went back for more, I could not believe I liked every item served on the buffet.  I highly recommend these place.  Who knew this gem was right in Lakewood.

data.title: Heavenly Vegetarian
data.text: My husband and I have been going to this restaurant since 2001. We just love the food. We are vegetarian and they have a great vegetarian selection as well as other non veg options. The food is delicious and served in generous portions. The family that owns this restaurant recognizes us and remembers our favorite order by heart (including no cilantro). I would recommend this restaurant and can't wait until my next visit!

data.title: Go to Subway Instead
data.text:
We have eaten Indian food throughout the United States as well as in Australia and New Zealand, and Great India Cuisine (totally ironic name) is pretty much the worst we have ever had and a bad value at that.

I asked what half a Tandoori chicken is, because there are so many variations of that dish from restaurant to restaurant. When I learned their version was thighs and drumsticks I passed.  I ordered the chicken Tikka also from the Tandoor menu and expected moist pieces of chicken.  I got a sizzling platter with raw onions and peppers. I was told that was the way it was served in India.  Not like any sizzling platter version I had ever had before.  I asked that they be cooked more.  Instead of nicely caramelized onions that I have had with other sizzling platters, I got greasy onions and peppers that had fairly heavy spice levels but still were not cooked. Their green chutney was fine.

However, the chicken tikka pieces were so dry that I had to order some raita to moisturize the chicken.  Their version is that the chicken tikka is breast meat, so of course it is going to be dry.    Given the short time it took for my entree to come out, there is no way that it was cooked to order. It was dry because it had been reheated.

My husband's chicken jalharzi (incorrect spelling) had ok chicken thigh meat, but it was a very small dish with very few vegetables.  He ordered it for the vegetables.

White basmati rice was totally unacceptional.  No saffron seasoning, and just a few black carraway seeds.

Our server was friendly and accommodating, and water was refilled, but none of that could make up for the poor food that cost $35 including a 15% tip.

Foot-long sandwiches at Subway would have been a better value and experience.  I can only believe that Great India Cuisine survives because there is no basis for comparison in Lakewood.

Definitely NOT recommended.

data.title: Satisfies The Need
data.text: Not the best we have ever had, but Great India is close and we get takeout every couple of months. Mom-Pop-Son operation....medium spicy is about right. We tried the very hottest one time and it was too spicy for us. Standard Indian fare. We think that the portions are pretty small for the price. But satisfies the need................

data.title: great food.
data.text: Good service. Friendly staff. Don't eat a lot of indian food to compare it to, but the food was fantastic. Not a lot of foot traffic so hope they stick around.

data.title: Excellent food with great flavor!
data.text: Had their lunch buffet. Flavors of the food were excellent. They could have a few more dish selections but everything I tried was good! I had a delicious warm chai tea to finish my lunch. Also many other gourmet teas to choose from. On high side $ wise for a buffet but well worth it.

data.title: Best Indian food in the South Sound!
data.text: The food here is outstanding. I have eaten at all the local Indian restaurants and Great Cuisine of India is, in my opinion, the best. Service is polite and attentive. Unlike some Indian places, the food at the lunch buffet is very flavorful and never bland. I have visited many times for both lunch and dinner, and have never been disappointed. My kids, who are generally picky eaters, love to go here as well. The Bhuna Chicken, Saag Paneer, and Lamb Korma are some of my favorites.

data.title: Very Good
data.text:
First, they had a lunch buffet that looked very good but I did not have it. Almost everything on the buffet was a Masala, chicken masala, meatball masala etc... I had the lamb Korma and it was delicious. My daughter had lamb vindaloo which she also liked (her favorite has always been lamb vindaloo) but she liked mine better.  The coconut lemonade was refreshing but a bit to sweet and overpriced at $4 a glass.  I ont know how much the buffet was but out lunches cost about $13 each.

I recommend this place and I will definitely be eating there again.

data.title: Average Indian Food.
data.text:
We stopped at Great India Cuisine on a early Friday evening for dinner.  While the service was excellent, the food was just so-so.  However, there are not many Indian restaurants in this area, so if you want to grab a bite, this would be your choice.  
They are closed in the afternoons from 2 to 4, so a late lunch is not an option.

data.title: Tasty
data.text: Had lunch here with my husband a few weeks ago. It was pretty good but I would order off of the menu next time and skip the lunch buffet. They had some great naan and paneer and other dishes. The mango lemonade was pretty good too. I think the menu items are probably tastier since they are fresher than the buffet. But the buffet was good and hot :)

data.title: Phenominal lunch buffet!!
data.text: This is best kept secret in Lakewood!! It's not a big place ( about 15 tables) and I haven't had the chance to go for their great dinner menu, but every chance I get, I go for  the lunch buffet. They make great butter chicken, and saag paneer, and tandoori chicken is always a staple on the lunch buffet. The meat dishes change each day, but I have yet to be disappointed. Most dishes aren't too spicy----they clearly label the spicy ones; and it goes great with their mango lemonade.  :)   I live in Lakewood, i've been going here for about 5 years, and have never been disappointed.
